  "slug": "internalized-as-skill",
  "title": "If the internalized other is the replacement form closest to what EFT builds (the felt sense of the partner's presence carried as an inner resource), can it be trained as a skill — or does it form only as a byproduct of enough time with a real other, making it a developmental achievement the therapy cannot provide, only one the person grows over time?",
  "url": "https://cambridgetcg.github.io/castle-gate/rooms/internalized-as-skill",
  "summary": "The child who was held enough carries the holding; the adult who was not must learn to hold himself — but can you teach a hand to do what only being held could build?",
